09/20/2016:


Texas banker takes big stake in Bravo Brio

Donald Adam, founder of the private equity firm TAC Capital LLC, bought up 15 percent of the Columbus-based Italian dining chain's stock in the past month. The position makes Adam the largest shareholder by far, owning more than three times as many shares as Bravo Brio founder and Chairman Alton Doody, the company's second-largest shareholder.
The new investor comes at a shaky time for Bravo Brio. .....

